<item>
            <title>[LU-4940] LFSCK 5: LFSCK needs to tolerate some OSP/OST connection issues</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4940</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, the LFSCK fix inconsistent OST-objects via OSP, and if the connection (or the peer) has trouble, related repairing request will return &quot;-ENOTCONN&quot; immediately, then the LFSCK will mark the LFSCK as LF_INCOMPLETE, and move to handle next one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Such model can make the LFSCK to process the inconsistent OST-objects ASAP, but it may cause the LF_INCOMPLETE to be marked too easy, which may be not the best choice. We can consider to make the LFSCK to wait for a while for the connection or peer to recover.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
